  "term": "def:supremum",
  "kind": "Definition",
  "title": "Supremum",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(S,\\le)$ be an ordered set, let $A \\subseteq S$, and let $s \\in S$. The element $s$ is the supremum of $A$ if and only if $s$ is an upper bound of $A$ and every upper bound $u$ of $A$ satisfies $s \\le u$.",
